{
  "stem": "12462.6",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They ought to be equalized downward, toward the-- the-- the lesser sentences.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And so, there were commutations, eventually, so that 10 years after the-- 10 years after the subsequent proceedings, hardly any of the remaining defendants were in jail.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "A few of them, as I say, in the medical case and in, I believe, the Einsatzgruppen case, were sentenced to death.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I had no direct responsibility for either of those cases, so I-- I'm-- my memory of the detail is not that great.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there's hardly a translation for that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] But it's-- the best we could do is call it 'Special Action Group'.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Einsatz really means substitute, mainly, in German.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And what it really meant was a special group designated to carry out some functions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And the main functions of the Einsatz groups, which were established under Himmler and the SS, were to fight the opposition, to go into the occupied countries and find the opponents-- and, of course, Jews and gypsies-- to run the concentration camps.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What kind of judges did you have in the subsequent proceedings?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Well, as-- as I-- [CLEARS THROAT] as I've said, there-- only in one-- in only two, and at the most three cases, were there death sentences.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There were a number of sentences for life.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Most of them were not served, they were commuted by McCloy later on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The judges themselves, though-- what kind of judges did you have?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, I thought you said-- well, the judges in the subsequent proceedings were mainly state court judges.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, all of them were from the United States.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The subsequent proceedings were entirely conducted-- well, with one exception, I can tell you-- were conducted entirely by Americans.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that meant American prosecutors and American judges.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
